deck: The wife of Tom DuBois and mother of Jazmine DuBois.
description:
History

Sarah grew up with her grandmother at a very young age. Later on the years, her grandmother was induced with a disease called the Patterson Syndrome; an extremely rare syndrome having similar effects of Leprechaunism. She was cured by the organization Ebony Brown (ex-girlfriend of Robert) runs for.

Relationship

She is usually caught on screen to be frustrated at Tom's unmasculine nature. She daydreams about men like Usher and Micheal Jackson, who have the qualities of being strong and successful.

Uncle Ruckus claims that Sarah married Tom out of pity. There wasn't actually true love in the process. Then again, Uncle Ruckus is racists and tends not to understand people for who they really are.

deck: Thomas "Tom" Lancaster DuBois is one of the main characters in The Boondocks. He is a calm, good-mannered African-American lawyer, and a close friend of Robert Freeman.
description:
Origin

Tom is shown to be a caring family man, who has a close relationship with his wife Sarah, and his daughter Jazmine. His hobbies were singing and playing the piano, dreaming to become a successful recording artist. Although his wife and friends don't find his singing amusing.

He played basketball on his Ivy League college team, but as Sarah points out he was mostly a bench warmer. His failures as a player, along with the influence of The Mighty Ducks film lead to coach a Woodcrest youth basketball team, failing to get a win for two years. He is also known as a "wet blanket" due to unable to lighten up.

Tom and his wife work for the NAACP and have strong understanding with the hardship of African Americans. Although he was a supporter in many African American issues, there're often times he contrasted. Such as a role as a prosecutor in "The Trail Of R.Kelly." And was temporarily convinced by Uncle Ruckus that he is a self-hating black man, as he can't stand certain black individuals such as Kobe Bryant, Usher, and others.

Tom follows the laws strictly, due to fears of being sent to jail and sexually assaulted by men. This fear came to Tom at a very young age from a television series that shows violent prison rape. It developed to such a degree that Tom refused to participate in even the slightest of legal crime, as a youth throughout adulthood. He eventually confronts his feats in "A Date With the Body Warrior" with the hopes of becoming a defense attorney.

Relationships

Sarah DuBois

The wife of Tom. Their relationship is portrayed unenthusiastic. Sarah doesn't like Tom's dull personality and Tom in-return finds Sarah insufferable. This leads her to over-like famous black musicians such as Usher, which Tom dislikes. Other than that, their marriage is loving and stable.

Jazmine DuBois

The daughter of Sarah and Tom. Tom and Jazmine have a close and loving relationship. But Tom is often shown to overly protect Jazmine quite a bit.

Robert Freeman

Good friend of Tom. Often seen hanging together although Robert does not show Tom the gratitude he shows. He makes fun of Tom time to time about his lack of masculinity and usually known as a social buzzkill. Tom, however, trust Robert and counts on him when in trouble, which Robert does not like as well.

Uncle Ruckus

Tom and Uncle Ruckus have a weird friendship due to Ruckus having a distaste of black people. But he has more respect for Tom than other black people because of his light skin, his education, and most of all his white wife. As others, they find Ruckus insufferable.

deck: A woman with a vengeful drive who also knows some luchador techniques. Occasionally acts as an enforcer for Dario Cueto.
description:
Origin

As a young girl her village was destroyed, its inhabitants slaughtered by a mysterious and powerful figure. Since then she swore vengeance and has hunted for information and clues as to who is responsible, hoping to get her revenge. Eventually Black Lotus would track leads to The Temple, home of the Dario Cueto's Lucha Underground fighting tournament. After confronting Dario about the death of her village, the sly and manipulative owner would protest innocence and feign ignorance. Black Lotus would later be abducted by Dragon Azteca and trained to be a luchador to better assist her wish of revenge.

Against Dragon Azteca's advice, she would preemptively attempt to find that very revenge by heading back to the temple. She would find herself confined in the same room as Dario Cueto's monstrous brother Matanza Cueto, who was also locked up. The manipulative Dario would seem to convince Black Lotus that it was in fact Dragon Azteca who was responsible for her villages destruction, and then she would appear to ally herself with him, and even become an enforcer of sorts for him. She would also end up killing Dragon Azteca. At the end of Season One of Lucha Underground, Dario is forced to flee the Temple, and Black Lotus would help him and his brother relocate.

Creation

Black Lotus is a fictional character developed for the El Rey Network produced Lucha Underground show. In 2016, several comic issues, designed to fill in plot points between Season One and Season Two of Lucha Underground were released. Black Lotus would appear alongside Dario Cueto, and his brother Matanza Cueto in Lucha Underground #4 - A Call for Blood, written by Justin Ortiz, Christopher Dejoseph and Fabian Rangel Jr.

Major Story Arcs

Season Two

Black Lotus returns to Lucha Underground, and acts as an enforcer for Dario Cueto when he also returns at Aztek Warfare II.
name: Black Lotus

deck: Chris is a student in Alexander Hamilton High School. He is lab partners with Viv.
description:
Major Story Arcs

Little Worse Than a Man

Once his lab partner Viv was absent for school after she was attacked by Grim Reaper, he approached her brother Vin and asked for her phone number to work on their chemistry project together. When Vin refused to give her number, Chris began to verbally assault him and Vin grabbed him by the neck and pushed a nerve center below the jawbone that caused Chris to become unconscious. This led to Vin being suspended.

Chris recovered from his injuries and talked to the now recovered Viv that he wasn't mad at her or her brother. It was implied that he may be romantically interested in Viv

Chris's father Leon Kinzky captured video of Virginia burying Grim Reaper, who she had murdered to defend her son. He tried to blackmail her and her family into leaving the neighborhood. When Virginia refused, and stepped towards Leon, he fired his gun at her. Virginia used her powers to phase through the bullets, which hit his son Chris, killing him
name: Chris Kinzky

deck: A retired solider who lives in Alexandria, Virginia, along with his son Chris.
description:
History

One night, Leon went over to Vision's house to introduce himself. This is due to Chris being the lab partner of Viv, Vision's daughter. When no one answered the door, he went around the house to the backyard to see if anyone was outside. Instead, he saw Virginia burying the body of the Grim Reaper. A villain that attacked the Visions earlier, whereas Virginia defended and accidentally killed him. Leon took a video of this and kept quiet. Some days later Vin, Vivi's brother, attacked Chris due to the distraught of the attack of the Grim Reaper. This incident left Vivi badly damaged.

Finding the synthezoids extremely dangerous, Leon blackmails Virginia into leaving the state. He sent her the video by mail, and called her every 2 pm. Virginia ignored the calls but later on picked it up, and Leon gave the address to meet her. Although she didn't knew it was Leon.

She followed the address of Leon's home that Leon told her on the phone and met the man that blackmailed her. Leon explained why he wanted Virginia to leave and if she didn't, he would expose the video of her burying the corpse. Virginia was furious at this proposal and approached him, until Leon drew a firearm. Out of protection he shot Virginia, but she phased through the bullets. At that moment, Chris just entered the room, awakened by his father's conservation. The shots that were meant for Virginia went through her as she phased and hit Chris, killing him instantly.

Leon approached his dead son, and blamed Virginia for the death. Swearing he won't rest until he rallies everybody to kill her family. Virginia who couldn't handle the anger within her knocked Leon cold. When the police came, they found Leon and Chris alone on the ground. Virginia had already fled the crime scene before the police caught her. Leon was eventually admitted to a hospital, where he remained in coma.
name: Leon Kinzky

description:
Origin

Steve is a park ranger that takes his job too seriously. He isn't exactly good at his job as he thinks although he is named "Ranger of the Month" every month, every year. He lives abide his title, never to let himself down and risk his job.

His father was also a park ranger in Brickleberry, having far better experience than his son, knowing the park inside out. Steve wanted to follow his father's footsteps becoming as him. But, after a couple of years his father went missing in the park, and ever since then Steve reconsidered if he really wanted to become a park ranger.

deck: Julia is adopted by Cardinal Farina as his daughter.
description:
Origin

Julia was an orphan from an Eastern tribe and sold to the Romans as a slave. Cardinal Farina bought her from the Haifa market. She became a kitchen maid who quickly rose above her station. Later, Farina adopted her as his daughter and often called her his little guardian angel.

Major Story Arcs

Magnus the Black had taken the offer to escort Cardinal Farina up north by taking the Black Road. After a group of armed men had overpowered Magnus the Black and killed Cardinal Farina, she nursed Magnus back to health. She asked to be taked up north in her father's place.

When, several days into their travel, they discover they're being followed by Kitta, the blacksmith from Iskfold, Julia turns on Magnus and shoots him several times with her crossbow. She escapes north.

deck: A malevolent entity bearing the appearance of Earth's Hero, Goku Black appeared in the timeline of Future Trunk's with the intent of eradicating humanity in the name of "justice". He was revealed to be none other than Zamasu, a rogue Kai from Universe 10, who had used the Super Dragon Balls to switch bodies with Goku.
description:
Origin

A figure who's identity surrounded in mystery and having the body of Goku, Black seeks to eradicate humanity, which he faults as the "greatest mistake of the Gods". He claims to have destroyed many civilizations, and arrived in Future Trunk's timeline to continue destroy humanity, in which he killed Future Bulma.

When Trunks escaped Black via his time machine, Black was able to follow him through a hole in space with the Ring of Time. It was there that he met the real Goku and fought him before being pulled back to his own time. He destroyed Trunks' time machine before he left, stranding his enemy in the past.

Creation

Black first appeared in the Dragon Ball Super anime episode 47: SOS From the Future! A New Black Enemy Appears!!

Black first appeared on the cover of the August 2016 issue of V Jump. He made a cameo appearance in Dragon Ball Super Chapter 14 (V Jump September 2016) while mostly cloaked in shadow attacking Trunks before the final big reveal (much like the anime).
name: Black Goku

deck: Mysterious man with a wolf like spirit companion.
description:
Origin

The man who refers to himself as Z.W.E.L. is mysterious in origin, his real name, age and origin unknown. Fear, suspicion and rumors do follow the fighter when he travels though, in part due to ZWEL's supernatural ability to summon a powerful and supernatural wolf like spirit creature, which he can either control or acts on his behalf. This ethereal ghostly creature is known as E.I.N. and although it can act in a near intangible way, it can interact with physical surroundings and deliver blows when desired. The two beings have not always been connected. ZWEL did not gain the ability to summon EIN until a violent encounter in which ZWEL refused the orders of a patron, Graf Dumas. Incensed by his refusal, Graf Dumas had ordered his men to lynch ZWEL and it was in near death that he received a mysterious brand and the ability to call forth EIN.

ZWEL would learn to move around frequently, and he would also eventually find friendship with fortune teller and fighter Viola. Then both would find assistance and aid by the powerful knight Siegfried.

Creation

Z.W.E.L. is fictional character created for the Soul Calibur franchise, created by publisher Bandai Namco. The mysterious fighter first appeared in Soul Calibur V released in 2012 and his design is attributed to Takuji Kawano.

Speaking of the character "I took two prototype characters designed by other designers, the "mysterious hooded man" and "vagrant in leather", and combined them with a base character model strong enough to support a 'silently burning desire for vengeance' while maintaining a calm and mature vibe." Some earlier concept designs of ZWEL suggests he may have been able to summon a variety of ethereal ghostly spirits.

Powers and Abilities

ZWEL utilizes a sword with three handles, and can summon EIN, a mysterious and ethereal wolf ghost that can perform a variety of attacks.
name: Z.W.E.I.

deck: Young ninja and student of Taki. Harbors a demon Arahabaki within her.
description:
Origin

Natsu is young ninja who was trained by the master ninja Taki. A member of the same clan as Taki, the Fu-Ma clan of ninja, she was destined to excel and trained to kill demons, however unfortunately a great demon was bound to Natsu. The great demon Arahabaki resided within her and because of this, many of the other Fu-Ma ninja clam members treated her with suspicion, fear and resentment. Some members of the clan would even try to assassinate her. The strong willed and honorable Taki however would defend, protect and speak on Natsu's behalf, which came to create a sense of appreciation and hero worship within Natsu towards Taki. Despite having a rebellious and anti-authortian personality, Natsu would always respect and honor her ninja master Taki. She would not always show that level of respect for other clan members.

At some point Taki would have to leave for a longer period of time for important work. Natsu would start to grow concerned as more time passed, and around that same time a young girl named Leixia would appear to the clan seeking assistance. A skilled fighter herself, Leixia would not find the fact that Natsu is possessed by a great demon terrifying, and would instead be curious fascinated. Natsu herself would find Leixia an endearing mix of awkward and sincere and so decide to be Leixia's bodyguard on her upcoming quest. The two girls would later come across nun chuck master Maxi and the staff wielding Xiba and as a group continue on together.

Creation

Natsu is fictional character created for the Soul Calibur franchise, created by the publisher Bandai Namco. The young ninja first appeared in Soul Calibur V released in 2012 and her design is attributed to Tomoko Imura. She is considered a legacy character, in the sense like many of the Soul Calibur V roster, she is a direct substitute for a former Soul Calibur character. She replaces Taki as a ninja styled character, and Taki herself is involved in the plot of Natsu. Speaking of the characters design Imura mentions, "The basic premise for Natsu's character was simplicity. I started with a rough draft and tried to figure out what which parts to keep, though that proved to be quite tricky. Natsu's fairly young so she may not have as much volume as Taki, but she's still growing"

Character Evolution

Natsu is effectively Taki's replacement in Soul Calibur V, one of the sequels in Namco's weapon based fighting games. Soul Calibur V introduced many new characters as substitutes for older characters, Natsu fulfilling the role of Soul Calibur's ninja expert. Originally Natsu was quite shy and timid, however the mentorship of Taki, gave her more confidence and bravado, especially after her training she received becoming of the more skilled and effective ninjas around.

Major Story Arcs

The Demon Arahabaki

At some point in the past, near the Izumo mountains, powerful demonic energies were noted, near one of the shrines at the location. The Fu-Ma ninja clan, and its leader Chie, became aware of this disturbance, and knew that a powerful demonic entity, Arahabaki was sealed there. Arahabaki is known as an ancient aborigine Japanese god, possessing shadowy spiritual powers and energies. It is known to manifest eight large electric snakes, in its physical form. She would send an experienced Fu-Ma clan ninja Juju to investigate. She would not return.

This would alarm Chie and she would arrange for various ninja clan heads to met and discuss the problem. The head of the Inobe faction would suggest crafting specific weapons to counter Arahabaki, but the head of the Fujibe clan, Shuke, was impatient and rashly decided to lead his entire clan out to attack and defeat Arahabaki. When she learned of this decision, Taki would quickly rush after the Fujibe clan, to catch up, but it would be too late, she would arrive to find the whole clan had been slaughtered. Only the Arahabaki possessed body of Juju stood before her, forcing Taki to battle her former clan member. The battle was intense, and brutal, but Taki would hesitate to use her most powerful dagger Mekki Maru, a vow she had made earlier. She would manage to kill the possessed Juju to stop Arahabaki. Unfortunately Arahabaki had not been destroyed, and had its spirit fled to a nearby village. Taki would track its demonic energy signature only to find the village in flames, destroyed with only one survivor, a small baby girl.

Recognizing the child as innocent and having some regret that she had not used Mekku Maru, Taki decided to seal Arahabaki inside the girl and to take her with her. Now Arahabaki would not threaten anyone else and the young girl would not have to be killed.

Powers and Abilities

Natsu is a trained and skilled ninja, and member of the demon hunting Fu-Ma ninja clan. Trained and mentored by the legendary ninja Taki, the greatest Fu-Ma ninja, Natsu is even more competent and skilled than most ninja. She wields two daggers, dual ninjato's, called Kuzukiri and Awayuki. She is practiced in Musoh-Battoh-Ryu. Natsu would be very fond of her weapons, as they were crafted and forged by Taki and her adoptive mother Chie.

Natsu is also is inhabited by a great demon, that is sealed inside her. Arahabaki. Although he is sealed within, his prescence within her also allows her certain supernatural abilities, she can use for various effect, like shockwaves and pillars of fire. Though Natsu knows to be careful, as each time she draws on such power, the demon Arahabaki regains strength, and one day may have enough strength to break through his bonds and take her over completely. Occasionally her appearance may alter to reflect the demon that resides inside her.

Physical Characteristics

  • Height: 5'4"
  • Weight: 114 lbs
  • Eyes: Green
  • Hair: Blonde

Other Media

Soul Calibur V (2012)

Natsu's first appearance came in the Namco video game, fighting franchise 2012's installment of Soul Calibur V. She is voiced by Fuyuka Ōura.

Project X Zone 2 (2015)

Natsu is the first Soul Calibur character to guest star in 2015's Project X Zone 2.
name: Natsu

deck: Practitioner of Ling-Sheng Su fighting style.
description:
Origin

Xiba is the child of the legendary fighters, Kilik and Xianghua. When Xianghua returned to her homeland of China, she was forced into an arranged marriage by her grandfather, Worried for her sons future, she asked her own father Mast Kong Xiuqiang to look after the boy. Kong Xiuqiang would teach the growing boy Ling-Sheng Su Secret Arts of the Rod, a staff based fighting martial arts. They would spend much time isolated in the mountains training, specifically Zhen Hang Mountain. Although he would become very gifted and skilled with a staff and attuned to nature and his own senses, Xiba would struggle with society and its ideas and so appear a bit feral in nature and attitude. A bit naive and sheltered, he approaches others with a pure and kind heart.

He would eventually become to befriend several other skilled fighters, Natsu, student of Taki, Leixia (who is actually his half sister) and Maxi. He would also be on a quest to find Kali-Yuga, a legendary staff and treasure.

Creation

Xiba is fictional character created for the Soul Calibur franchise, created by Bandai Namco. The feral fighter first appeared in Soul Calibur V and his design is attributed to Takuji Kawano and Daishi Odashima.
name: Xiba
